How much would $TSLA need to grow to justify today’s valuation?  Using the 7% profit margin, working backwards, you get about 215B in sales, which represents a 700% increase from 2020 projected sales, or about a 50% annualized growth rate sustained for the next 5 years.

$TSLA still has not produced a profitable year or proved it can operate with that kind of margin, but assume they get there.  A mature valuation for TSLA might be around 20x earnings and even that is generous for an auto maker. (Toyota trades at 10x earnings).

$TSLA at $1600 per share provides a valuation of approx 300B to Tesla.  In FY 2019, TSLA had 25B in sales, which is projected to grow to about 30B for 2020.  Assuming Tesla can operate with a margin comparable to $TM of about 7%, that would equate to 2.1B in net profit.
